<h2>
	Average Nucleotide Identity
</h2>
<p>
	Average Nucleotide Identity (<abbr title="Average Nucleotide Identity">ANI</abbr>) is a measure of nucleotide-level genomic similarity between the coding regions of two genomes. <abbr title="Bidirectional best hits">BBH</abbr>s between a genome pair are computed as pairwise bidirectional best nSimScan hits of genes having 70% or more identity and at least 70% coverage of the shorter gene.
</p>
