<h3>
	Statistics
</h3>
<p>
	The alignment fraction (AF) and average nucleotide identity (ANI) have been computed for <strong>[% xcount %]</strong> genomes and <strong>[% ycount %]</strong> genome pairs.</p>
	<p><strong>[% zcount %]</strong> pairs of these are between genomes assigned to the same taxonomics species.
</p>
<p>
	Maximal clique enumeration generates <strong>[% acount %]</strong> clusters, including <strong>[% bcount %]</strong> genomes from <strong>[% ccount %]</strong> taxonomic species.</p>
<p><strong>[% dcount %]</strong> genomes from <strong>[% ecount %]</strong> species are singletons.
</p>
[%	END %]
